text: Harold Newhart (July 19, 1903 - March 31, 1977) was an American gymnast. He competed in seven events at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1903 births Category:1977 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Parkersburg, West Virginia
